section.section:
Subject to the provisions of this subsection, the Commission may suspend, by order, any methods of advertising real estate brokerage services or soliciting listings of houses for the purpose of resale or rental in a real estate conservation area if the Commission determines that:
the area would benefit by the suspension;
the suspension would advance a State interest;
there is a reasonable basis to believe that panic selling, blockbusting, or depressed real estate market values would occur without the suspension; and
there is no less restrictive alternative available.
